definition: strong/powerful/better/slightly more than/vigorous/violent/best in their category, e.g. see 百強|百强[bai3 qiang2]
to force/to compel/to strive/to make an effort
to flow/to disseminate/to circulate or spread/to move or drift/to degenerate/to banish or send into exile/stream of water or sth resembling one/class, rate or grade

sentences.english: A simple method for the estimation of the transverse shielding for intense- beam proton linac was described briefly.
sentences.chinese: 叙述了估算强流质子直线加速器横向屏蔽的方法。

sentences.english: Therefore it is necessary to design an intense beam accelerator in line with the equipartitioning principle.
sentences.chinese: 因此，有必要按照‘均温’的原则设计强流加速器。

sentences.english: Rip currents are so strong that they can carry swimmers away from shore before they know what's happening.
sentences.chinese: 强流来势凶猛，会在不知不觉问把游泳者卷走。

sentences.english: Computer simulation study on the design of the coupling cell in an RFQ with intense beams.
sentences.chinese: 强流射频四极加速器耦合单元的物理设计研究。

sentences.english: A radial insulation structure which is used in long pulse high current diode is introduced in this paper.
sentences.chinese: 介绍了一种应用于长脉冲强流二极管的径向绝缘结构。
